HEADWORD: Theoretics
<hw>The`o*ret"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The speculative
part of a science; speculation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At the very first, with our Lord himself, and his apostles, as
represented to us in the New Testament, morals come before
contemplation, ethics before <qex>theoretics</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>H. B.
Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

